abstract: HARTFORD, May 31.--Mrs. John Chidsey and her sister, Maria Avant, were found murdered in their house in Avon this morning. Mrs. Chidsey was in her room up stairs on a bed, and a Bible was lying by her side. She was struck with a blow by a tailor's goose. The other woman, who was in the kitchen, was killed by a blow from an axe.

abstract: FLORENCE, May 28.--That strenuous belief in social caste which finds practical expression in the family feeling, "Stand aside; I am better than you," is the dry-rot of British civilization. abstract: The fifteenth annual regatta of the Atlantic Yacht Club was sailed yesterday under rather unfavorable circumstances, the lack of wind leaving most of the handsome yachts floating helplessly with the tide. abstract: CINCINNATI, June 15.--The storm of last night was the severest that has been experienced in this part of the country for 12 years. The rainfall here was two and one-third inches in two hours, and at points north of this city it was even more severe. Reports from along the railroad and telegraph lines tell of unprecedented floods, of telegraph wires down, bridges washed away, trees uprooted, and crops laid flat upon the earth.

abstract: The Austrian bark Treci Dubrovacki arrived in the Lower Bay from Port de Paix, Hayti, late Wednesday evening. abstract: KINGSTON, N.Y., June 29.--The army-worm has made its appearance in myriads along the line of the Wallkill Valley Railroad, destroyring every green thing that comes in its path.
